Zoo expert Royev Ruchei on Thursday takes care of a female polar bear in Norilsk, Russia. The bear was discovered in the Norilsk industrial area for the first time in 40 years. The animal, listed in the Russian Red Data Book as an endangered species, wandered into the city hundreds of miles away from its natural habitat in the Arctic. Photo: VCGÂ  
